## PART 4 — FRONTEND ↔ BACKEND CONNECTION ISSUES

### 🚨 Critical

| # | File | Issue | Fix |
|---|------|-------|-----|
| 1 | `ReceivePage.jsx` L36 | Uses **relative URL** `fetch("/api/v1/simulation/...")` instead of `API_BASE` from `api.js`. Vite dev server on `:5173` will proxy this to itself, **not to the backend on `:8000`** | Use the `request()` helper from `api.js` or prefix with `http://127.0.0.1:8000` |
| 2 | `vite.config.js` | **No proxy configured**. Frontend runs on `localhost:5173`, backend on `127.0.0.1:8000`. Without a Vite proxy, all relative URLs fail | Add a `server.proxy` config to forward `/api` → `http://127.0.0.1:8000` |

### ⚠️ Moderate

| # | File | Issue |
|---|------|-------|
| 3 | `api.js` L1 | `API_BASE` is **hardcoded** to `http://127.0.0.1:8000`. Should use an env variable (`import.meta.env.VITE_API_URL`) for flexibility |
| 4 | `api.js` | No **auth token** is attached to requests — the `request()` helper doesn't read/send JWT from localStorage, so all authenticated endpoints will fail |
| 5 | `ReceivePage.jsx` L40–41 | Sends `sender_id = receiver_id = localStorage.getItem("user_id")` and `token_id: "demo"`. The UUID `"demo"` is invalid and will crash the backend |

